<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Make a Carrot Clarinet</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="span">Clarinets are a musical instrument from the woodwind family .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1004" relname="span">The clarinet is classified by its cylindrical shape and the type of mouthpiece</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="3" relname="elaboration">used</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="purpose">to play it .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1006" relname="contrast">Traditional clarinets are made from plastic or wood in a factory ,</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="span">but you can make one at home for fun ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="means">using just a carrot !</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="preparation">Buy a large carrot .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="span">It should be quite large</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="11" relname="elaboration">( 190mm or longer ) .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1013" relname="preparation">This carrot should be sturdy and not soft .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1013" relname="joint">Gather other supplies .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="preparation">Get a clarinet or saxophone mouthpiece , reed , and ligature .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1015" relname="joint">Get a kitchen knife , vegetable peeler , and funnel .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">Get a tube</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="17" relname="elaboration">that is 12mm in diameter</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1018" relname="elaboration">cut to 35mm long and some electrical tape .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Get an electric drill with a 12mm spade bit and a 7mm drill bit .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Cut the ends of the carrot off .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1016" relname="sequence">The length of the carrot should come to about 187mm .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1016" relname="sequence">Mark 6 holes on the front of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1023" relname="joint">The 1st hole should be 39mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1023" relname="joint">The 2nd hole should be 54mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1026" relname="span">The 3rd hole should be 74mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="26" relname="elaboration">The 4th hole should be 97mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="span">The 5th hole should be 123mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">The 6th hole should be 140mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1023" relname="joint">Mark one hole on the back for your thumb .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1023" relname="joint">The thumbhole should be 22mm from the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1031" relname="sequence">Drill through the center of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1031" relname="sequence">Use the 12mm spade bit</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1031" relname="sequence">and drill straight down the center of the carrot from top to bottom .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="36" relname="condition">As you drill ,</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1035" relname="span">dump the contents of the inside of the carrot into the bowl .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="span">Drill</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="circumstance">until there is a clear path from one end of the carrot to the next .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1038" relname="sequence">Drill the 6 holes on the front of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1040" relname="span">Use the 7mm drill bit</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="40" relname="purpose">to drill each of the marked 6 holes through to the center of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1042" relname="span">Drill the 1 hole on the back of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1043" relname="span">Use the 7mm drill bit</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="span">to drill the 1</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="44" relname="elaboration">marked hole through to the center of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1046" relname="span">Use a vegetable peeler</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="46" relname="purpose">to peel off a layer over the holes on the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="span">This created a slightly flat part of the carrot</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="elaboration">that will home the finger and thumb holes for the clarinet .</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="preparation">Attach a 12mm tube to the bottom of the mouthpiece .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1054" relname="condition">If the tube does not stay in the mouthpiece ,</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1054" relname="span">wrap a piece of electrical tape around the end of the tube</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="52" relname="purpose">to widen the wall of the tube .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1053" relname="elaboration">( Some mouthpieces will fit differently from others . )</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1051" relname="span">Attach the 12mm tube and mouthpiece to the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1050" relname="joint">The opposite end of the tube should fit inside of the top of the carrot .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="span">Add a funnel to the bottom of the carrot ,</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="57" relname="condition">if desired .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1059" relname="joint">The funnel makes the carrot look more like a clarinet</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1059" relname="joint">and amplify the sound a little bit .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1059" relname="elaboration">The carrot is playable without the funnel .</segment>
